<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-01-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-01-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="87" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d87">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 836/46.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Chargé <persName type="to">Lorillard</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-01-10"><hi rend="italic">January 10,
                                1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Bacon states that the action of the President of Brazil decreeing
                            the continuance of the preferential tariff is highly appreciated as
                            evidence of friendly good will.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>